{
  "mergedContent": "Identity: 40-year-old former headman of Lisle; skilled rider with possible military background; stoic, pragmatic, stubborn to the point of self-destruction; from border region—knows Karsite features and tactics.\nState: Newly awakened immensely powerful Mage-Gift (unknown type, possibly Firestarting)—burned open mental channels cause white-hot agony, blurred vision, teetering sanity; Gift-shock severe, caused four-day unconsciousness during journey; now at Haven Healers' Collegium, unconscious but stable; memories of Lisle destruction blocked/suppressed.\nArc: Witnessed entire village destroyed and people carried off during bandit attack; believes others caused destruction—doesn't yet fully accept he did it himself; driven by duty to warn Haven despite trauma; initially dismissed Senta as 'insufferable horse,' called her for mercy killing → accepted Companion bond, shifted to partnership ('we face it together'); ordered Senta to knock him out if he loses control—accepts danger he poses.\nStance: [Senta] Chosen by her—bond snapped into place when their eyes locked; her unconditional love and mental bridges stabilized his fracturing mind enough to survive; accepts bond pragmatically but resists excessive care; their connection allows mind-speech though it pains his ragged channels; affectionate partnership ('we face it together').\nEvidence gathered: Red robes hidden under bandit clothing; suspects organized sect, not simple bandits; tracks lead toward Menmellith; theories captives meant for blood magic ritual sacrifice (old Karsite practice).",
  "canonicalName": "Rance"
}
